    </div>
    <button class="hint-toggle" onclick="showHintShor('h71')">show hint</button>
    <div class="feedback hint" id="h71">M/N = 768/1024 = 3/4 in lowest terms (gcd(768,1024)=256). Denominator = 4 = P.</div>
    <div class="feedback" id="fb71"></div>
  </div>
</div>
</section>

<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<!-- SECTION 8 — COMPLETE EXAMPLE n=15 -->
<!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<section class="section" id="s8">
<div class="section-num">Section 08</div>
<h2>Complete Example: Factorize n = 15</h2>

<p>Let us trace through the complete Shor algorithm for n = 15, using x = 7.</p>

<h3>Setup</h3>

<div class="math-block">
  <div class="mstep">
    <div class="mstep-label">f(ℓ):</div>
    <div class="mstep-body">f(ℓ) = 7<sup>ℓ</sup> mod 15 ∈ &#123;0, 1, …, 15&#125; → values need 4 bits</div>
  </div>
  <div class="mstep">
    <div class="mstep-label">Choose N:</div>
    <div class="mstep-body">N > n² = 225, and N must be a power of 2 → <strong>N = 1024 = 2¹⁰</strong>, so log₂ N = 10 qubits</div>
  </div>
  <div class="mstep">
    <div class="mstep-label">Pick x=7:</div>
    <div class="mstep-body">gcd(7, 15) = 1 ✓ (so 7 shares no factor with 15)</div>
  </div>
</div>

<h3>① Building the initial superposition</h3>

<div class="math-block">
  <div class="mstep">
    <div class="mstep-label">Initial state:</div>
    <div class="mstep-body">|ψ₀⟩ = |0⟩ ⊗ |0⟩ ⊗ … ⊗ |0⟩ &nbsp; (10 qubits + 4 qubits)</div>
  </div>
  <div class="mstep">
    <div class="mstep-label">After H<sup>⊗10</sup>:</div>
    <div class="mstep-body">|ψ₀⟩ = |0⟩ ⊗ <span class="scalar">1/√1024</span> (|0⟩ + |1⟩ + |2⟩ + … + |1023⟩)</div>
  </div>
</div>

<h3>② Evaluating f and its period</h3>

<div class="math-block">
  <div class="mstep">
    <div class="mstep-label">f(0) = 1</div>
    <div class="mstep-body">f(1) = 7 &nbsp;&nbsp; f(2) = 4 &nbsp;&nbsp; f(3) = 13 &nbsp;&nbsp; f(4) = 1 &nbsp;&nbsp; f(5) = 7 &nbsp;&nbsp; …</div>
  </div>
  <div class="mstep">
    <div class="mstep-label">Period:</div>
    <div class="mstep-body"><span class="c-g">P = 4</span> &nbsp;&nbsp; (since f(4) = f(0) = 1)</div>
  </div>
</div>

<h3>③ State after U_f</h3>

<div class="math-block">
  <div class="mstep">
    <div class="mstep-label">|ψ₁⟩ =</div>
    <div class="mstep-body">
      <span class="scalar">1/√1024</span> (|1⟩|0⟩ + |7⟩|1⟩ + |4⟩|2⟩ + |13⟩|3⟩ + |1⟩|4⟩ + |7⟩|5⟩ + …)
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<h3>④ Measure lower register: suppose we get |4⟩ (= f(2))</h3>

<div class="math-block">
  <div class="mstep">
    <div class="mstep-label">Collapse:</div>
    <div class="mstep-body">
      State becomes: |ψ₂⟩ ∝ |4⟩(|2⟩ + |6⟩ + |10⟩ + |14⟩ + …)<br>
      Upper register is uniform over &#123;2, 6, 10, 14, …&#125; — arithmetic sequence with step P=4.
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<canvas id="cvShorState" width="560" height="170"></canvas>
<div class="canvas-caption">Upper register after measuring f(a)=4: non-zero amplitudes at positions 2, 6, 10, 14, … (step P=4). The QFT will reveal this period.</div>

<h3>⑤ Apply QFT₁₀₂₄ to upper register</h3>

<div class="math-block">
  <div class="mstep">
    <div class="mstep-label">QFT reveals:</div>
    <div class="mstep-body">
      Peaks at positions 0, N/P, 2N/P, 3N/P = 0, 256, 512, 768<br>
      (since N = 1024, P = 4, N/P = 256)
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mstep">
    <div class="mstep-label">Measurement:</div>
    <div class="mstep-body">Suppose we measure M = 768</div>
  </div>
</div>

<canvas id="cvShorQFT" width="560" height="160"></canvas>
<div class="canvas-caption">After QFT₁₀₂₄: peaks at 0, 256, 512, 768. Each has equal probability 1/P = 1/4 = 25%.</div>

<h3>⑥ Extract P from M = 768</h3>

<div class="math-block">
  <div class="mstep">
    <div class="mstep-label">Compute M/N:</div>
    <div class="mstep-body">M/N = 768/1024 = 3/4 &nbsp;&nbsp; (in lowest terms)</div>
  </div>
  <div class="mstep">
    <div class="mstep-label">Read off P:</div>
    <div class="mstep-body">Denominator = 4 = <span class="c-g">P</span> ✓</div>
  </div>
</div>

<h3>⑦ Check and extract factors</h3>

<div class="math-block">
  <div class="mstep">
    <div class="mstep-label">r = P = 4:</div>
    <div class="mstep-body">r is even ✓</div>
  </div>
  <div class="mstep">
    <div class="mstep-label">Check:</div>
    <div class="mstep-body">(x<sup>r/2</sup> + 1) mod n = (7² + 1) mod 15 = 50 mod 15 = 5 ≠ 0 ✓</div>
  </div>
  <div class="mstep">
    <div class="mstep-label">Factors:</div>
    <div class="mstep-body">
      gcd(7² − 1, 15) = gcd(48, 15) = gcd(3, 15) = <span class="c-g">3</span><br>
      gcd(7² + 1, 15) = gcd(50, 15) = gcd(5, 15) = <span class="c-g">5</span><br>
      <strong>15 = 3 × 5</strong> ✓ 🎉
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

